claim.claim-text:
21. A communications system, comprising: 
a plurality of base stations which transmit respective pilots and respective code channels comprising a forward traffic channel; 
a mobile station which has the plurality of base stations assigned to an active set thereof, comprising: 
a diversity receiver which measures respective signal qualities of the pilots; 
a processor which produces a signal quality standard, prepares a message directing one of the base stations to transmit data on its respective forward traffic channel when the quality of the pilot of the one base station equals or surpasses the standard, and prepares a message directing more than one base station to transmit data simultaneously on their respective forward traffic channels when the quality of a single pilot of any of the base stations does not equal or surpass the standard; and 
a transmitter which transmits the message to the system controller via the plurality of base stations; 

a system controller communicatively connected to the plurality of base stations and maintaining data queues for the mobile station's forward traffic data in those base stations contained in the mobile station's active set; 
wherein the one base station receives, and transmits in response to, a message directing the one base station to transmit data from its data queue on its respective forward traffic channel; and 
wherein the system controller receives a message directing more than one base station to transmit data simultaneously on their respective forward traffic channels and directs the respective base stations accordingly.

23. A base station, communicatively connected to a base station controller, a plurality of other base stations, and one or more mobile stations, comprising: 
a transmitter for transmitting pilots and code channels comprising a forward traffic channel; and 
a receiver for receiving messages from a mobile station; 
wherein the base station receives, and transmits in response, to a message directing it to transmit data on its forward traffic channel; 
wherein the base station receives from a mobile station and delivers to the base station controller a message directing more than one base station to transmit simultaneously on their respective forward traffic channels; and 
wherein the base station transmits accordingly under direction of the base station controller.
